b'PM: The speech I made today was about making sure we boost the drivers of opportunity: family, education & work.\nhttps://t.co/KDxCw44yri'

b'PM: By taking on govt failure & backing family, education & work we extend opportunity & could change the lives of many disadvantaged people'
b'PM: We will help more people back into work and increase the minimum wage to \xc2\xa36.70 from October 2015.'

b'PM: Families are the best welfare system there is. In the next 5 years we will double free childcare for 3 & 4 yrs olds with working parents'

b"PM: I'm here in Runnymede on the banks of the Thames. 800 years ago on this spot, King John sealed the #MagnaCarta.\nhttps://t.co/t2NUYt1xA3"
b"Read PM's #MagnaCarta speech in full: http://t.co/7p8g1XSPNB http://t.co/p4VR0JyQTL"
b'PM: So on this historic day, let\xe2\x80\x99s pledge to keep those principles alight. Let\xe2\x80\x99s keep #MagnaCarta alive.'
b'PM: Liberty, justice, democracy, the rule of law \xe2\x80\x93 we hold these things dear and  they took shape right here by the Thames. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: #MagnaCarta is something every person in Britain should be proud of. Its copies may be faded, but its principles shine as brightly.'
b'PM: The seeds sown here have grown throughout the world. In America; in India with Gandhi and South Africa with Nelson Mandela. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: The clauses inspiring those who fought in the English Civil War, giving fuel to the Chartists, succour to the Suffragettes. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: This great charter shaped the world for the best part of a millennium helping to promote arguments for justice and freedom. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: What is taken for granted here in Britain, is what others are crying out for, hoping for, praying for. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: The countries that have these things tend to be the long term successes. Those who don\xe2\x80\x99t tend to be the long term failures. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: All over the world, people are still struggling to live by the rule of law and to see their governments subject to that law. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: What happened here eight centuries ago is as relevant today as it was then. And that relevance extends far beyond Britain. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: The limits of executive power, guaranteed access to justice, the rule of law, shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t be imprisonment without trial. #MagnaCarta'
b'PM: 800 years ago, on this day, King John put his seal to a document that would change the world. #MagnaCarta'
